      <article class="about-copy">
        <h2>What WPCNA is</h2>
        <p>The White Plains Council of Neighborhood Associations coordinates neighborhood associations across White Plains and helps keep communication open between neighborhoods, city government, and the public.</p>
        <blockquote class="mission-quote">The White Plains Council of Neighborhood Associations coordinates the neighborhood associations in White Plains, NY. Its purpose is to enhance the quality of life in the City, and in particular, in its neighborhoods. As an advisory council, the WPCNA functions by disseminating information and opinion to the public and public officials, and by encouraging local action.</blockquote>

        <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
        <p>White Plains has a busy downtown, active neighborhood associations, public meetings, local organizations, and city notices moving at the same time. This site is meant to pull the most useful pieces together in one place so residents can see what is happening, find neighborhood context, and stay connected to public life around the city.</p>
        <p>That is why the site brings together White Plains events, a guide to the city's neighborhoods, meeting agendas, and a few practical pages people tend to need again and again.</p>

        <h2>How residents use it</h2>
        <p>You can use this site to follow neighborhood-relevant events, get a clearer sense of different parts of White Plains, review WPCNA agendas, and send information to the council for possible posting. It is meant to be useful, plainspoken, and easy to check without digging through several different sites.</p>
        <p>WPCNA itself is made up of representatives from neighborhood associations throughout White Plains. The council serves as a place to share information, raise concerns, and keep neighborhoods in touch with each other and with the wider community.</p>
      </article>

      <div>
        <figure class="about-photo">
          <img src="{{ site.aboutImage | withPrefix }}" alt="{{ site.aboutImageAlt }}" loading="lazy">
        </figure>

        <div class="sidebar-card" id="contact-form">
          <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
          <h3>Get in touch</h3>
          <p>Questions, updates, or neighborhood news can be sent here.</p>
          <form class="contact-form" action="{{ site.contactFormAction }}" method="POST">
            <input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="{{ site.contactFormSubject }}">
            <input type="hidden" name="_captcha" value="false">
            <input type="hidden" name="_template" value="table">

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-name">Name</label>
              <input id="contact-name" name="name" type="text" autocomplete="name" required>
            </div>

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-email">Email</label>
              <input id="contact-email" name="email" type="email" autocomplete="email" required>
            </div>

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-subject">Subject</label>
              <input id="contact-subject" name="topic" type="text" required>
            </div>

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-message">Message</label>
              <textarea id="contact-message" name="message" rows="6" required></textarea>
            </div>

            <button class="btn btn-primary btn-block" type="submit">Send message</button>
          </form>
        </div>

